The Plateau state Governor Simon Lalong has emerged as the chairman of the 19 northern governors Forum. His emergence followed the expiration of the outgoing Chairman of the forum Borno State Governor Kashim Shettima. Reading the communique  at the end of the forum ‘s Meeting, Kashim Shettima said the governor would take over his new position with effect on 29 May, 2019. The new Chairman of the forum in his acceptance speech thanked his colleagues for the gesture bestowed on him. He also promised not to betray their trust as he also commended the outgoing Chairman Kashim Shettima who he described as very hard working ‎Leader. Details later… Kaduna: 19 Northern governors to elect new chairman as meeting commences Shettima visits late Mamman Nasir's family Army/IPOB clash: Northern govs hail residents for peace Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin